{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":825,"text":"A few years ago,"},{"time":2747,"text":"my mom developed rheumatoid arthritis."},{"time":6989,"text":"Her wrists, knees and toes swelled up,\ncausing crippling, chronic pain."},{"time":14391,"text":"She had to file for disability."},{"time":16734,"text":"She stopped attending our local mosque."},{"time":19516,"text":"Some mornings it was too painful\nfor her to brush her teeth."},{"time":24339,"text":"I wanted to help."},{"time":26500,"text":"But I didn't know how."},{"time":28716,"text":"I'm not a doctor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31005,"text":"So, what I am is a historian of medicine."},{"time":35930,"text":"So I started to research\nthe history of chronic pain."},{"time":39957,"text":"Turns out, UCLA has an entire\nhistory of pain collection"},{"time":44002,"text":"in their archives."},{"time":46593,"text":"And I found a story --\na fantastic story --"},{"time":50069,"text":"of a man who saved -- rescued --\nmillions of people from pain;"},{"time":55889,"text":"people like my mom."},{"time":58772,"text":"Yet, I had never heard of him."},{"time":60256,"text":"There were no biographies\nof him, no Hollywood movies."},{"time":64483,"text":"His name was John J. Bonica."},{"time":69070,"text":"But when our story begins,"},{"time":70642,"text":"he was better known as\nJohnny \"Bull\" Walker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76611,"text":"It was a summer day in 1941."},{"time":79857,"text":"The circus had just arrived\nin the tiny town of Brookfield, New York."},{"time":85486,"text":"Spectators flocked to see\nthe wire-walkers, the tramp clowns --"},{"time":89431,"text":"if they were lucky, the human cannonball."},{"time":92190,"text":"They also came to see the strongman,\nJohnny \"Bull\" Walker,"},{"time":96098,"text":"a brawny bully who'd pin you for a dollar."},{"time":100467,"text":"You know, on that particular day,\na voice rang out"},{"time":103432,"text":"over the circus P.A. system."},{"time":105441,"text":"They needed a doctor urgently,\nin the live animal tent."},{"time":109302,"text":"Something had gone wrong\nwith the lion tamer."},{"time":111710,"text":"The climax of his act had gone wrong,"},{"time":114863,"text":"and his head was stuck\ninside the lion's mouth."},{"time":119629,"text":"He was running out of air;"},{"time":121312,"text":"the crowd watched in horror"},{"time":123503,"text":"as he struggled and then passed out."},{"time":126788,"text":"When the lion finally did relax its jaws,"},{"time":130073,"text":"the lion tamer just slumped\nto the ground, motionless."},{"time":135813,"text":"When he came to a few minutes later,"},{"time":138206,"text":"he saw a familiar figure hunched over him."},{"time":141169,"text":"It was Bull Walker."},{"time":143816,"text":"The strongman had given the lion tamer\nmouth-to-mouth, and saved his life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150864,"text":"Now, the strongman hadn't told anyone,"},{"time":152716,"text":"but he was actually\na third-year medical student."},{"time":156788,"text":"He toured with the circus\nduring summers to pay tuition,"},{"time":160474,"text":"but kept it a secret\nto protect his persona."},{"time":163787,"text":"He was supposed to be\na brute, a villain --"},{"time":167215,"text":"not a nerdy do-gooder."},{"time":170535,"text":"His medical colleagues didn't\nknow his secret, either."},{"time":173156,"text":"As he put it, \"If you were\nan athlete, you were a dumb dodo.\""},{"time":177849,"text":"So he didn't tell them about the circus,"},{"time":180344,"text":"or about how he wrestled professionally\non evenings and weekends."},{"time":186353,"text":"He used a pseudonym like Bull Walker,"},{"time":188997,"text":"or later, the Masked Marvel."},{"time":191627,"text":"He even kept it a secret that same year,"},{"time":195159,"text":"when he was crowned\nthe Light Heavyweight Champion"},{"time":198542,"text":"of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":201313,"text":"Over the years, John J. Bonica\nlived these parallel lives."},{"time":206515,"text":"He was a wrestler;"},{"time":208233,"text":"he was a doctor."},{"time":209788,"text":"He was a heel;"},{"time":211334,"text":"he was a hero."},{"time":213038,"text":"He inflicted pain,"},{"time":214858,"text":"and he treated it."},{"time":217242,"text":"And he didnâ€™t know it at the time,\nbut over the next five decades,"},{"time":220768,"text":"he'd draw on these dueling identities"},{"time":223610,"text":"to forge a whole new way\nto think about pain."},{"time":227620,"text":"It'd change modern medicine\nso much so, that decades later,"},{"time":231774,"text":"Time magazine would call him\npain relief's founding father."},{"time":237351,"text":"But that all happened later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240179,"text":"In 1942, Bonica graduated\nmedical school and married Emma,"},{"time":245815,"text":"his sweetheart, whom he had met\nat one of his matches years before."},{"time":250505,"text":"He still wrestled in secret -- he had to."},{"time":253781,"text":"His internship at New York's\nSt. Vincent's Hospital paid nothing."},{"time":259101,"text":"With his championship belt,\nhe wrestled in big-ticket venues,"},{"time":262877,"text":"like Madison Square Garden,"},{"time":264838,"text":"against big-time opponents,"},{"time":266538,"text":"like Everett \"The Blonde Bear\" Marshall,"},{"time":269411,"text":"or three-time world champion,\nAngelo Savoldi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274192,"text":"The matches took a toll on his body;"},{"time":276993,"text":"he tore hip joints, fractured ribs."},{"time":280295,"text":"One night, The Terrible Turk's big toe\nscratched a scar like Capone's"},{"time":285217,"text":"down the side of his face."},{"time":287302,"text":"The next morning at work,\nhe had to wear a surgical mask to hide it."},{"time":292450,"text":"Twice Bonica showed up to the O.R.\nwith one eye so bruised,"},{"time":297088,"text":"he couldn't see out of it."},{"time":299138,"text":"But worst of all were\nhis mangled cauliflower ears."},{"time":304094,"text":"He said they felt like two baseballs\non the sides of his head."},{"time":309153,"text":"Pain just kept accumulating in his life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313177,"text":"Next, he watched his wife go\ninto labor at his hospital."},{"time":317509,"text":"She heaved and pushed, clearly in anguish."},{"time":321657,"text":"Her obstetrician called\nout to the intern on duty"},{"time":324125,"text":"to give her a few drops of ether\nto ease her pain."},{"time":327519,"text":"But the intern was a young guy,\njust three weeks on the job --"},{"time":330904,"text":"he was jittery, and in applying the ether,"},{"time":333864,"text":"irritated Emma's throat."},{"time":336145,"text":"She vomited and choked,\nand started to turn blue."},{"time":340895,"text":"Bonica, who was watching all this,\npushed the intern out of the way,"},{"time":346259,"text":"cleared her airway,"},{"time":347864,"text":"and saved his wife\nand his unborn daughter."},{"time":352172,"text":"At that moment, he decided\nto devote his life to anesthesiology."},{"time":357414,"text":"Later, he'd even go on to help develop\nthe epidural, for delivering mothers."},{"time":362850,"text":"But before he could focus on obstetrics,"},{"time":365009,"text":"Bonica had to report for basic training."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370373,"text":"Right around D-Day,"},{"time":371991,"text":"Bonica showed up\nto Madigan Army Medical Center,"},{"time":375237,"text":"near Tacoma."},{"time":376783,"text":"At 7,700 beds, it was one of the largest\narmy hospitals in America."},{"time":382242,"text":"Bonica was in charge\nof all pain control there."},{"time":385618,"text":"He was only 27."},{"time":388470,"text":"Treating so many patients,\nBonica started noticing cases"},{"time":391788,"text":"that contradicted everything\nhe had learned."},{"time":394976,"text":"Pain was supposed to be\na kind of alarm bell -- in a good way --"},{"time":399846,"text":"a body's way of signaling an injury,\nlike a broken arm."},{"time":404538,"text":"But in some cases,"},{"time":406174,"text":"like after a patient had a leg amputated,"},{"time":409673,"text":"that patient might still complain\nof pain in that nonexistent leg."},{"time":414231,"text":"But if the injury had been treated, why\nwould the alarm bell keep ringing?"},{"time":418861,"text":"There were other cases in which there\nwas no evidence of an injury whatsoever,"},{"time":423014,"text":"and yet, still the patient hurt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426678,"text":"Bonica tracked down all the specialists\nat his hospital -- surgeons,"},{"time":430670,"text":"neurologists, psychiatrists, others."},{"time":433782,"text":"And he tried to get\ntheir opinions on his patients."},{"time":437643,"text":"It took too long, so he started organizing\ngroup meetings over lunch."},{"time":443123,"text":"It would be like a tag team of specialists\ngoing up against the patient's pain."},{"time":447613,"text":"No one had ever focused on pain\nthis way before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452928,"text":"After that, he hit the books."},{"time":455845,"text":"He read every medical textbook\nhe could get his hands on,"},{"time":458732,"text":"carefully noting every mention\nof the word \"pain.\""},{"time":462282,"text":"Out of the 14,000 pages he read,"},{"time":466187,"text":"the word \"pain\" was\non 17 and a half of them."},{"time":470908,"text":"Seventeen and a half."},{"time":472934,"text":"For the most basic, most common,\nmost frustrating part of being a patient."},{"time":478875,"text":"Bonica was shocked -- I'm quoting him,"},{"time":481006,"text":"he said, \"What the hell kind of conclusion\ncan you come to there?"},{"time":485484,"text":"The most important thing\nfrom the patient's perspective,"},{"time":488690,"text":"they don't talk about.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":491295,"text":"So over the next eight years,\nBonica would talk about it."},{"time":495209,"text":"He'd write about it; he'd write\nthose missing pages."},{"time":498057,"text":"He wrote what would later be known\nas the Bible of Pain."},{"time":502575,"text":"In it he proposed new strategies,"},{"time":506016,"text":"new treatments using\nnerve-block injections."},{"time":509614,"text":"He proposed a new institution,\nthe Pain Clinic,"},{"time":512381,"text":"based on those lunchtime meetings."},{"time":515248,"text":"But the most important thing\nabout his book"},{"time":517683,"text":"was that it was kind of an emotional\nalarm bell for medicine."},{"time":522486,"text":"A desperate plea to doctors\nto take pain seriously"},{"time":528491,"text":"in patients' lives."},{"time":531321,"text":"He recast the very purpose of medicine."},{"time":535373,"text":"The goal wasn't to make patients better;"},{"time":539582,"text":"it was to make patients feel better."},{"time":544955,"text":"He pushed his pain agenda for decades,"},{"time":547066,"text":"before it finally took hold\nin the mid-'70s."},{"time":550831,"text":"Hundreds of pain clinics sprung up\nall over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555711,"text":"But as they did -- a tragic twist."},{"time":559754,"text":"Bonica's years of wrestling\ncaught up to him."},{"time":564597,"text":"He had been out of the ring\nfor over 20 years,"},{"time":566773,"text":"but those 1,500 professional bouts\nhad left a mark on his body."},{"time":571769,"text":"Still in his mid-50s, he suffered\nsevere osteoarthritis."},{"time":576360,"text":"Over the next 20 years\nhe'd have 22 surgeries,"},{"time":580403,"text":"including four spine operations,"},{"time":582954,"text":"and hip replacement after hip replacement."},{"time":586110,"text":"He could barely raise\nhis arm, turn his neck."},{"time":590144,"text":"He needed aluminum crutches to walk."},{"time":593879,"text":"His friends and former students\nbecame his doctors."},{"time":597923,"text":"One recalled that he probably\nhad more nerve-block injections"},{"time":602149,"text":"than anyone else on the planet."},{"time":606043,"text":"Already a workaholic,\nhe worked even more --"},{"time":609505,"text":"15- to 18-hour days."},{"time":611922,"text":"Healing others became more\nthan just his job,"},{"time":614455,"text":"it was his own most effective\nform of relief."},{"time":618510,"text":"\"If I wasn't as busy as I am,\"\nhe told a reporter at the time,"},{"time":622345,"text":"\"I would be a completely disabled guy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":627423,"text":"On a business trip to Florida\nin the early 1980s,"},{"time":630986,"text":"Bonica got a former student to drive\nhim to the Hyde Park area in Tampa."},{"time":637338,"text":"They drove past palm trees\nand pulled up to an old mansion,"},{"time":641506,"text":"with giant silver howitzer cannons\nhidden in the garage."},{"time":646895,"text":"The house belonged to the Zacchini family,"},{"time":649858,"text":"who were something like\nAmerican circus royalty."},{"time":654229,"text":"Decades earlier, Bonica had watched them,"},{"time":656826,"text":"clad in silver jumpsuits and goggles,"},{"time":659737,"text":"doing the act they pioneered --\nthe Human Cannonball."},{"time":664772,"text":"But now they were like him: retired."},{"time":669267,"text":"That generation is all dead\nnow, including Bonica,"},{"time":672862,"text":"so there's no way to know exactly\nwhat they said that day."},{"time":676475,"text":"But still, I love imagining it."},{"time":679233,"text":"The strongman and the human\ncannonballs reunited,"},{"time":682510,"text":"showing off old scars, and new ones."},{"time":685802,"text":"Maybe Bonica gave them medical advice."},{"time":688082,"text":"Maybe he told them what he later\nsaid in an oral history,"},{"time":693432,"text":"which is that his time in the circus\nand wrestling deeply molded his life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701286,"text":"Bonica saw pain close up."},{"time":705236,"text":"He felt it. He lived it."},{"time":708453,"text":"And it made it impossible\nfor him to ignore in others."},{"time":713449,"text":"Out of that empathy, he spun\na whole new field,"},{"time":716587,"text":"played a major role in getting\nmedicine to acknowledge pain"},{"time":719723,"text":"in and of itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722627,"text":"In that same oral history,"},{"time":724563,"text":"Bonica claimed that pain"},{"time":727096,"text":"is the most complex human experience."},{"time":732215,"text":"That it involves your past life,\nyour current life,"},{"time":736053,"text":"your interactions, your family."},{"time":739256,"text":"That was definitely true for Bonica."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742593,"text":"But it was also true for my mom."},{"time":748043,"text":"It's easy for doctors to see my mom"},{"time":751366,"text":"as a kind of professional patient,"},{"time":754652,"text":"a woman who just spends her days\nin waiting rooms."},{"time":759714,"text":"Sometimes I get stuck seeing her\nthat same way."},{"time":765076,"text":"But as I saw Bonica's pain --"},{"time":767067,"text":"a testament to his fully lived life --"},{"time":771623,"text":"I started to remember all the things\nthat my mom's pain holds."},{"time":778370,"text":"Before they got swollen and arthritic,"},{"time":782162,"text":"my mom's fingers clacked away"},{"time":785501,"text":"in the hospital H.R. department\nwhere she worked."},{"time":789150,"text":"They folded samosas for our entire mosque."},{"time":794734,"text":"When I was a kid, they cut my hair,"},{"time":798459,"text":"wiped my nose,"},{"time":800935,"text":"tied my shoes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809832,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811181,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}